                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">859A.20/213: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister to the Norwegian Government in Exile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at London</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-26T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 26, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Norwegian Series No. 15. Your 17.<note n="18" xml:id="d24fn18">Dated August 13,
                        11 p.m.; not printed.</note> War Department approves draft exchange of notes
                    as telegraphed in your no. 16 and recommends that agreement be consummated as
                    soon as possible. Accordingly, you are authorized to proceed with exchange of
                        notes<note n="19" xml:id="d24fn19">The notes exchanged between Minister
                        Biddle and Mr. Lie, the Norwegian Minister for Foreign Affairs, on August 28
                        were the same as draft quoted in Norwegian Series telegram No. 16, July 9, 7
                        p.m., <ref target="#pg_12">p. 12</ref>. For final text of notes, see
                        Department of State Executive Agreement Series No. 497, or 59 Stat. (pt. 2)
                        1819.</note> “acting under instructions of your Government”.</p>
                <p>Texts of notes as signed should be sent to Department by air mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
